{
  "answer": "**Manusmṛti Chapter 3** offers the strongest counter-current, extolling the *honoring* of women—by fathers, brothers, husbands, and brothers-in-law—as essential to household prosperity and divine favor.[^1] The text warns that families where women grieve quickly perish, while those where they do not always prosper; sacred rites fail without such honor.[^2] Women are radiant lights of the home, and spousal contentment ensures progeny and fortune.[^3]\n\nWhile Chapter 9 indeed stresses lifelong male *protection* of women (Mn. 9.3), it frames this as guarding lineage purity amid assigned feminine traits like \"crookedness,\" yet balances it by deeming women \"worthy of honor,\" \"lights of the house,\" and \"goddesses of fortune,\" vital for procreation, rites, pleasure, and ancestral heaven (Mn. 9.26–28).[^4] Husbands protect wives to safeguard *their own* dharma, progeny, and self (Mn. 9.6–7), and women manage household wealth, purification, duties, cooking, and effects (Mn. 9.11).[^5] Virtuous wives reach their husband's worlds (Mn. 9.29).[^6]\n\nThese passages nuance dependency as *reciprocal reverence* and *functional agency* in the home—echoing Helena's quest as divinely sanctioned triumph, not mere autonomy, but prevailing under imperial/Christian auspices.\n\nThe Falsafa corpus lacks *Elene*'s full text here (only metadata confirms Cynewulf's poem), so no direct cross-corpus link; Manu's tensions alone sustain the argument.\n\n[^1]: *Manusmṛti*, Chapter 3, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/03/translation/#p-d37889).\n\n[^2]: *Manusmṛti*, Chapter 3, [paragraphs](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/03/translation/#p-91f6ca).\n\n[^3]: *Manusmṛti*, Chapter 3, [paragraphs](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/03/translation/#p-91f6ca).\n\n[^4]: *Manusmṛti*, Chapter 9, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/09/translation/#p-a00cec).\n\n[^5]: *Manusmṛti*, Chapter 9, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/09/translation/#p-76576d).\n\n[^6]: *Manusmṛti*, Chapter 9, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/09/translation/#p-6c8c98).",
